<p><span style="font-size: 14px">Job Corps is a free residential education and training program for youth ages 16 to 24 who qualify as low-income. The program helps young people learn a career, earn a high school diploma or GED certificate, and find a good job. Job Corps provides the all-around skills needed to succeed in a career and in life.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 14px">Since 2006, Job Corps has made a significant commitment to training students for good-paying healthcare jobs.&nbsp; Over 90 Job Corps Centers offer healthcare career technical education opportunities in one or more of the following career training programs:</span></p><ul><li><span style="font-size: 14px"><strong><em>Clinical Medical Assistant</em></strong></span></li><li><span style="font-size: 14px"><strong><em>Dental Assistant</em></strong></span></li><li><span style="font-size: 14px">Dietary Technician</span></li><li><span style="font-size: 14px">Emergency Medical Technician</span></li><li><span style="font-size: 14px"><strong><em>Licensed Practical/Vocational Nurse</em></strong></span></li><li><span style="font-size: 14px">Medical Insurance Specialist</span></li><li><span style="font-size: 14px">Medical Laboratory Assistant</span></li><li><span style="font-size: 14px">Medical Laboratory Technician</span></li><li><span style="font-size: 14px"><strong><em>Medical Office Support</em></strong></span></li><li><span style="font-size: 14px"><strong><em>Nurse Assistant/Home Health Aide</em></strong></span></li><li><span style="font-size: 14px">Opticianry</span></li><li><span style="font-size: 14px">Paramedic</span></li><li><span style="font-size: 14px">Patient Care Technician</span></li><li><span style="font-size: 14px"><strong><em>Pharmacy Technician</em></strong></span></li><li><span style="font-size: 14px">Physical Therapy Aide</span></li><li><span style="font-size: 14px">Radiology Technician</span></li><li><span style="font-size: 14px">Registered Nurse</span></li><li><span style="font-size: 14px">Rehabilitation Technician</span></li><li><span style="font-size: 14px">Respiratory Technician</span></li><li><span style="font-size: 14px">Respiratory Therapy Aide</span></li><li><span style="font-size: 14px">X-Ray Technology</span></li></ul>
<p><span style="font-size: 14px">Programs in <strong><em>bold italics</em> </strong>are offered at ten centers of more.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 14px">A list of Job Corps Centers by State is available using this <em><a href="javascript:popit('job-corps/centers')">Center List.</a></em>&nbsp; A 2011 list of which Job Corps Centers offer the each of the above Healthcare Training Programs is provided under <em><a href="javascript:popit('job-corps/training-programs')">Training List.</a></em></span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 14px"><strong>Interested in Joining Job Corps?</strong></span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 14px">If you or someone you know is interested in joining Job Corps, call <strong>(800) 733-JOBS</strong> or <strong>(800) 733-5627</strong> where an operator will provide you with general information about Job Corps, refer you to the admissions counselor closest to where you live, and mail you an information packet.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 14px">In addition, Job Corps student videos are available on: <a href="javascript:popit('http://recruiting.jobcorps.gov/en/Home.aspx')">http://recruiting.jobcorps.gov/en/Home.aspx</a></span></p>